t226.text: While all of this became imperative because of my care responsibilities, I’ve been reading all the #FlattenTheCurve material and feel that since I’m in a position to do so these are responsible pro-social actions to take.

t227.text: I emailed my local federal MP and requested that she lobby within govt to expand access to more subsidised absences as many children with be withdrawn from childcare and without more absences these workers will lose income.

t228.text: I emailed my after school care provider and explained the situation and assured her I’d keep our place open and keep paying for it. We have thirty days of subsidised care absences left before mid year. That’s 15 weeks care for us.

t229.text: I emailed my small kid’s school and told them that I’d be pulling her out of school within the week. I asked for some guidance on what resources we can access at home and an idea of what we should be aiming to cover. Again, I’m lucky to be in a position to do this & keep working.

t230.text: I emailed my boss and requested that I move towards work from home arrangements this week. I recognise how lucky I am to be in a job and workplace that makes this possible.

t231.text: Having binged on virus-related content all weekend, I made some decisions today. All informed by the fact that I am the primary carer for an elderly person who’s vulnerable on multiple counts.
